If you want to user ftp
sudo apt-get install ftp

then it will work as sftp

In Windows remember to change your working directory BEFORE connecting

cd  mypath/folder

ftp myserveraddress

the will ask for username and then password

to download files:

get myfile.txt

if you have to dwonload multiple files :

mget myfile.txt myfile2.txt


to upload files from your local working directory:

put myfile.txt
